race.comment: KISSAVOS (6) kept fresh and he looks back on track after scoring a slick 1050m trial win at Randwick on October 20. Blinkers and lugging-bit go on third-up. Hard to hold out. POMBIA (9) placed this course and distance and backs-up quickly. Came out fast on the good tempo before weakening to run sixth over 1100m at Hawkesbury. Visors go on and she can grip on late to take a hand in the finish. DEAR MY FRIEND (1) nice debut after the three trials when sticking on late to secure second over 1000m at Orange. Big jump in class but gets a much better run today. Each way. EMPRESS IRENE (5) Brutal filly from Isabella Snowflake on debut for the Beer & Carpenter stable. Showed enough in her only trial when third over 805m at Kembla Grange. Cross over nose band goes and will need luck from the gate.
